# Function Documentation Rules
- All function documentation must be written in English
- Each function must have a clear description of its purpose
- Document all parameters including their types and purpose
- Document the return value and its type
- Include examples of usage when the function is complex
- Document any side effects or important behaviors
- Specify any exceptions that might be thrown
- Keep documentation up to date with function changes
- Use consistent formatting across all function documentation
- Include performance considerations for complex functions
